    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5c43ddc6-f572-41c9-b308-2ed2a38d94e0\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n2. press `w` to open a window\n3. press `w` again to close the window (The rightmost edge of the screen has a vertical window separator column❌)\n4. keep pressing `w` (The newly opened window suddenly has a smaller size❌)\n5. keep pressing `w` (The window with `winfixwidth` set is expanding unexpectedly❌)\n\nminimal.lua:\n\n```\nlocal open_win = function()\n\treturn\n\tvim.api.nvim_open_win(\n\t\t0,\n\t\tfalse,\n\t\t{\n\t\t\twin = -1,\n\t\t\tsplit = \"right\",\n\t\t\twidth = 20,\n\t\t}\n\t)\nend\n\nlocal win1\nwin1 = open_win()\nvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"winfixwidth\", true, {win = win1})\n\nlocal win2\nlocal toggle_win2 = function()\n\tif win2 == nil then\n\t\twin2 = open_win()\n\telse\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_win_close(win2, true)\n\t\twin2 = nil\n\tend\nend\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"w\", toggle_win2)\n\nvim.o.winbar = \"%{%v:lua.wn()%}\"\nwn = function()\n\treturn vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()\nend\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\neliminate all ❌\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1948+gc53e00889d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.13.5-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly",
