            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This seems to be a Vim bug, unrelated to `nvim_open_win`:\n\n```vim\nfunc! s:open_win() abort\n  botright vsplit\n  vert resize 20\n  let w = win_getid()\n  wincmd p\n  return w\nendfunc\n\ncall setwinvar(s:open_win(), '&winfixwidth', 1)\n\nlet s:w2 = 0\nfunc! s:toggle_win2() abort\n  if s:w2 == 0\n    let s:w2 = s:open_win()\n  else\n    execute win_id2win(s:w2) 'close'\n    let s:w2 = 0\n  endif\nendfunc\n\ncall s:toggle_win2()\ncall s:toggle_win2() \" last window still has a vsep\n\n\" smash w and the width of last window increases\nnnoremap w <Cmd>call <SID>toggle_win2()<CR>\n```",
